The leader of the INRI Evangelical Spiritual Church, Lagos, Primate Elijah Babatunde Ayodele has advised President Muhammadu Buhari not to disappoint Nigerians for re-electing him for another four years. In a statement in Ado Ekiti, the spokesman clergy, Mr. Kehinde Balogun also revealed that the cleric actually predicted President Muhammadu Buhari as the winner of the February 23 presidential and national assembly elections conducted by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). He urged the President to urgently embark on people-oriented programmes that would put smiles on the faces of the poor masses, fight corruption, insecurity that still make part of the country unsecured. The clergy said a lot is being expected of him in delivering dividends of democracy to the electorate. Governor Fayose attacks Buhari again, blames him for Nigeria''s woes Anglican Primate urges patience for Buhari Clergy wants support for anti-graft war